Definition.WordDefinition: Omahas \O"ma*has"\, prop. n. pl.; sing. {Omaha}. (Ethnol.) A tribe of Indians who inhabited the south side of the Missouri River. They are now partly civilized and occupy a reservation in Nebraska. [1913 Webster]

Definition.WordDefinition: Maha \Ma"ha\, prop. n. (Ethnol.) A member of the Siouan people formerly living in the Missouri river valley in Northeastern Nebraska; called also {Omaha}. [WordNet 1.5]

Omaha n 1: a member of the Siouan people formerly living in the Missouri river valley in northeastern Nebraska [syn: {Maha}] 2: largest city in Nebraska; located in eastern Nebraska on the Missouri river; a major transportation center of the Midwest 3: the Dhegiha dialect spoken by the Omaha people 4: thoroughbred that won the triple crown in 1935
